I know that 'Girls Like Us' has aired about three years ago, but the film's legacy lives on! My mom taped 'Girls Like Us' for me, and I still watch it. I really feel like I personally know the girls in the documentary. The problems that they had to deal with were serious, and unfortunately these problems are often left ignorant to parents and teachers because it is not easy to discuss some of these serious issues with adults. I think this documentary has opened the eyes to many young adults and older adults. Hopefully, a gap has bridged between parents and children through the viewing of 'Girls Like Us'. 
